
[1]scurrilous

   SCUR'RILOUS, a.

   1. Using the low and indecent language of the meaner sort of people, or
   such as only the licence of buffoons can warrant; as a scurrilous
   fellow.

   2. Containing low indecency or abuse; mean; foul; vile; obscenely
   jocular; as scurrilous language.
